 <title>Project Structure</title>
 <abstract>
  <para>
   A Build Service project is a consistent collection of software packages
ready for end-user installation from repositories.  Usually, those repositories
are available for one or more versions of one or more Linux distributions.  All
dependecies are resolved by dedicated building single packages for all these
systems.  To accomplish the building procedure, you must arrange some meta
data.
  </para>
